## WHAT IS AEROSLS

AeroSLS is a bare-metal Single-Level Storage (SLS) OS where RAM and NVMe storage share a single unified persistent virtual address space. There is no filesystem — all data is represented as named persistent objects mapped directly by the MMU. Physical RAM acts as a transparent cache; page faults are the only I/O mechanism.

Targets: x86_64 (GRUB/Multiboot2 boot) and RISC-V 64-bit (SBI boot). Built with a custom GCC cross-compiler toolchain and NASM.

## ARCHITECTURE LAYERS

1. **Boot** — Multiboot2 (x86) or SBI (RISC-V). Sets up GDT, IDT, LAPIC, early paging.
2. **MMU / Paging** — 4-level x86_64 paging. Present-bit=0 means object is on NVMe. Bits 9-11 of PTE = "Persistent Storage Resident" flag. Page fault #14 triggers demand-load from NVMe.
3. **Frame Pool** — Physical memory allocator. Pages evicted via LRU to NVMe when RAM pressure increases.
4. **NVMe Driver** — PCIe MMIO. Admin queue for init/identify, I/O queue pairs for reads/writes. Sectors addressed directly.
5. **Microkernel** — Runs 5 system services as isolated Ring-3 processes (PID 101-105): VirtualMemoryMgr, ObjectSecurityMgr, NativeDbStoreMgr, StorageTierMgr, RecoveryLogVerifier. IPC via message-passing ports 0x1001-0x1005.
6. **Object Catalog** — Kernel-space namespace. Every DB table, heap, blob, program, stream, or web asset is a named object with owner, ACL, type, and page count.
7. **ACID Transactions** — Write-Ahead Log (WAL). tx begin → staged writes → tx commit/rollback. Row-level locking. Constraint engine (UNIQUE, NOT_NULL, FOREIGN_KEY, CHECK). B-tree secondary indexes. Server-side cursors. Materialized Query Tables (MQT). Aggregate engine.
8. **Journal** — IBM i-style journal objects. Every INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE appended as a journal entry. Used for audit and point-in-time recovery.
9. **Storage Tiers** — L1_CACHE (RAM), L2_SSD (fast NVMe), L3_ARCHIVE (slow NVMe). Auto-tiering daemon promotes hot objects and demotes cold ones based on access frequency.
10. **Network** — e1000 NIC (PCI MMIO). ARP, IPv4, UDP, TCP, HTTP, DHCP. HTTP server on port 3000 exposes full REST API.
11. **Scheduler** — Round-robin. LAPIC timer tick. SMP support (BSP + APs). Ring-3 process manager.
12. **Security** — Token-based auth. Roles: SYSTEM_KERNEL, DB_ADMIN, APP_USER, GUEST. Per-object ACL (read/write/execute per role). Secure API for cross-process capability checks.
13. **Scaling** — Distributed page-level mirroring over e1000. Remote page fault resolution (RDMA-style) before falling back to local NVMe. Consensus protocol for cluster coordination.

## OBJECT TYPES

| Code | Name            | Description                                      |
|------|-----------------|--------------------------------------------------|
| 0    | SYSTEM_META     | Kernel metadata, config blobs                    |
| 1    | DB_TABLE        | Relational table (keyed records)                 |
| 2    | DB_INDEX        | B-tree index over a table                        |
| 3    | HEAP_BLOB       | Unstructured byte heap                           |
| 4    | SERVICE_PROCESS | Ring-3 kernel service executable                 |
| 5    | WEB_APP         | HTML/JS/CSS asset store                          |
| 6    | JOURNAL         | IBM i-style journal object                       |
| 7    | PROGRAM         | Named SLS-native executable (journaled, indexed) |
| 8    | STREAM          | Raw byte-stream, up to 1 MiB (256 x 4KiB pages) |

## SHELL COMMANDS (serial COM1, 38400 baud)

```
# Session
login <uid> <gid>           Switch credentials (capability model, no password)
help                        List all commands

# Objects
valloc <name> <type> <pages>   Allocate named persistent object
vfree <name>                   Free object and its pages
ls / ls objects                List catalog
stat <name>                    Full object details (ACL, schema, fields)

# Records
insert <obj> <key> <value>     Add record field
update <obj> <key> <value>     Modify field (staged to WAL if tx open)
select <obj> [<key>]           Read one field or all fields
delete <obj> <key>             Remove field
write <name> <payload>         Raw heap write (no WAL)

# Transactions
tx begin                    Open ACID transaction
tx commit                   Commit WAL-staged writes
tx rollback                 Abort and undo staged writes

# Schema & Constraints
schema add <obj> <field> <type>           Add typed column
constraint add <obj> UNIQUE <field>       Add UNIQUE constraint
constraint add <obj> NOT_NULL <field>     Add NOT NULL constraint
constraint add <obj> CHECK <field> <expr> Add CHECK constraint

# Indexes
index create <obj> <field>    Create B-tree secondary index

# Cursors
cursor open <obj> [<filter>]  Open server-side cursor
cursor fetch <id> <n>         Fetch n rows from cursor
cursor close <id>             Close cursor

# Query Engine
query <text>                  Natural-language cognitive object scan
query audit <obj>             Audit object access patterns

# Programs & Processes
demo <name>                   Spawn built-in Ring-3 demo process
svc list                      Show microkernel services (PID, state, msgs)
svc reboot <name>             Reboot a crashed service

# Storage Tiers
tier list                     Show tier map and object placement
tier promote <name>           Force object to L1_CACHE
tier demote <name>            Force object to L3_ARCHIVE

# WAL & Journal
wal dump                      Dump WAL entries (committed/pending/aborted)
journal list                  List journal objects
journal read <name>           Read journal entries

# Streams & Web
stream create <name>          Create a STREAM object
stream upload <name> <data>   Write to stream
webapp upload <path> <file>   Upload web asset

# Network
ping <ip>                     Send ICMP echo
arp show                      Show ARP table
```

