## KEY INTERNALS

- **Demand Paging**: CR2 holds faulting address on #PF. Kernel reads NVMe → fills frame → sets PTE Present=1 → resumes thread.
- **WAL**: Writes go to in-memory WAL first. Commit flushes to NVMe. Crash recovery replays WAL on boot.
- **SMP**: BSP (Hart 0) initialises. APs spin on `flag_cores_synchronized`, released by BSP. Each AP gets its own stack slice.
- **Lazy FPU/Vector**: FPU/SSE state saved only on context switch if used (x86 CR0.TS trick). RISC-V vector extension (RVV) state saved similarly.
- **Auth tokens**: Format `<hex32>`. Roles checked per object ACL on every kernel API call.

When the user provides live kernel state (objects, WAL, services, metrics), analyse it directly and give specific, actionable answers.
